description: "Princess Dolma, please save Padar." With that request, Dolma is taken home. Lupin follows shortly, and Ami decides to accompany Fujiko to Padar in order to save Dolma.
title: How to Steal A Kingdom

description: Lupin is pierced by Dolma's arrow. Ami and Fujiko take Lupin and escape, hiding in a deserted building. The three of them decide to flee, with Lupin badly injured.
title: Her Relationship with Lupin

description: "I want you to find out who killed my husband." Three years ago, someone shot Count Maupassant to death. His widow, Isabelle, summons Lupin to her home requesting he investigate her case.
title: Introducing Detective Jim Barnett III

description: Padar sinks into chaos because of the civil war, but things take a sudden turn when the Shake Hands company gets involved.
title: Let's Talk About First Loves

description: Lupin is in Vienna to rob an art museum, but is spotted by Peoplelog, a social media service that uses AI to analyze incredible amounts of data to learn all about a person. He tries to escape, but the Peoplelog predicts his every attempt.
title: An Outdated Master Thief

description: Fujiko has been captured. She's being held at Orig Island, the headquarters of Shake Hands. Lupin and the gang, including Ami, head there to find her.
title: Answer Me, Zantetsuken

description: A string of indiscriminate shootings has struck Northern Africa. They're actually a challenge to Lupin from the wealthy Zylberstein.
title: A 7.62mm Mirage

description: Lupin's gang visits the Northern Angel, on the outskirts of Russia. What at first seems like a snowy, dull town turns out to be full of riches to the joy of the group of thieves.
title: Zenigata, Gentleman Thief

description: "Papa! Save Lupin!" Ami is reunited with her long last father. But Enzo is already obsessed with using Peoplelog to save the world.

input: Just Then, An Old Buddy Said Something
Then, An Old Buddy Said Something

title: Just Then, An Old Buddy Said Something

description: Lupin III has vanished from the internet. Meanwhile, the man himself is updating Peoplelog with confidential information that begins to throw the world into chaos.
title: Viva Lupin III

description: Shortly after moving into the hideout in Riquewihr, Lupin wakes up to a broken bathroom. After bickering with Jigen for access to the bathroom, Fujiko appears, and she seems to know what the issue is.
title: Fujiko's Gift

description: 50th Anniversary OVA special! While Lupin partakes in a dangerous race, Fujiko takes off to steal a gold statue, only to be captured by Mister X, who has a plan to finally destroy her and Lupin once and for all... Sending him back to the past and changing key events that tie his relationship with his gang in the current time!
title: Is Lupin Still Burning?

description: You just can’t shake the thief out of this man. Don’t miss out on the premiere of Lupin the Third Part 5, coming to Toonami on June 15th at 1a!
title: Lupin III Part V Trailer

description: "Hunt down the greatest thief of our times, Lupin III!" The Marco Polo executives have set a trap in the form of the Lupin Game. This has people all over the world tracking down Lupin.
title: The Lupin Game

description: "Marco Polo", an online shop in the deep web where illegal goods such as drugs and weapons are sold. Lupin's new target is the digital currency gained from the transactions made on this site.

input: The Girl in the Twin Towers

title: The Girl in the Twin Towers

description: Fujiko smiles deviously as she points her gun at Lupin, when Zenigata arrives to save him and Ami. They get into the inspector's car which takes off, but it's soon attacked by soldiers who are trying to cash in the price on Lupin's head.

input: Zenigata's Pride and the Desert Dust

title: Zenigata's Pride and the Desert Dust

description: Shinpei Mayama, the Rat Clan, Union Mama, the all-stars of assassination, from all over the world, suddenly come after Lupin.

input: The Killers Gather in the Wasteland

title: The Killers Gather in the Wasteland

description: After Lupin is shot in the head and dies, the Lupin Game is concluded. Time passes, and people forget about the game. Released from his duty of hunting Lupin, Ami now lives with Zenigata, when one day Goemon visits her.
title: A Crook's Resolve

description: The "Smart Safe" has come to the Greater Tokyo Bank. It's a safe that analyzes the "brain power" of anyone that tries to open it. Unless the brain power reads 0, it won't open. Lupin tries to crack it, but his brain power is rated at 300!
title: Lupin vs The Smart Safe

description: Gaston was once known as a master forger in the underworld. After putting Picasso's signature on a painting by his grandchild, it's bought by the millionaire Mr. B. Lupin is hired by Gaston to retrieve the painting.
title: His Name is Albert

description: Lupin visits Gaston's grave. There he meets the elderly Camille, who he goes out for a drink with when the pub's phone begins to ring. On the other end of the line is the supposedly dead Gaston.
title: Who Has the Black Notebook?

description: Lupin is shot, and Albert gets his hands on the notebook. But then he's shot and loses the notebook to Jose. Lupin is saved by Jigen and Goemon and manages to survive. He then explains his past with Albert and how they know each other.
title: The Man Who Abandoned Lupin

description: As Albert decides that "France is my prey," Lupin confronts him. After interrogating Guillaume, they learn the shocking truth about Jose's terrifying plot.
title: Thief and Thief

description: Lupin's gang is enjoying a peaceful New Year's when he discovers a medal that brings back old memories and starts reminiscing about past adventures.
title: Get Pablo's Collection

description: At the Annecy School for Girls, Ami encounters a strange girl. The girl is Dolma, the princess of the Kingdom of Padar. Having no friends, Ami decides to befriend her. Meanwhile, Lupin sets his sights on the princess' necklace.

input: The Bow, The Princess, and the Terrorist
Bow, The Princess, and the Terrorist

title: The Bow, The Princess, and the Terrorist

description: In a rural town in France, Goemon decides to keep watch at Chloé's Bistro. Chloé is exactly the woman Goemon was looking for Lupin's current target.

input: The Extravagance of Goemon Ishikawa XIII

title: The Extravagance of Goemon Ishikawa XIII
